snippet: Officials insisted that no traders benefited from the accidental distribution of minutes from their March meeting, which were sent to a virtual Who’s Who of Wall Street firms.
abstract: Federal Reserve alerts bank officials that policy makers are considering shift on when to begin easing back on stimulus efforts; minutes from meeting are released publicly a day before after Fed official mistakenly e-mailed them to virtual Who's Who of Wall Street firms, but Fed insists there is no evidence Wall Street traders benefited from what is called an error.
lead_paragraph: Officials insisted that no traders benefited from the accidental distribution of minutes from their March meeting, which were sent to a virtual Who’s Who of Wall Street firms.

headline.seo: Fed Officials Discussed Early End of Easing
headline.main: By Accident, Fed Gives Early Data to Banks
headline.print_headline: In Accident, Fed Gives Early Data To Banks
